    <section xml:id="curl_show_network_neutron">
        <title>Show network or subnet details with cURL</title>
        <para>You can request a JSON or XML response when you issue a request in a cURL command.</para>
        <procedure>
            <title>To show information in a JSON response for a specified network ID</title>
            <step>
                <para>Issue the following cURL command:
                    <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><?db-font-size 65%?>
                            <prompt>$</prompt> curl https://dfw.servers.api.rackspacecloud.com/v2.0/$account/networks/{id} \
        -X GET \
        -H "X-Auth-Project-Id: $account" \
        -H "Accept: application/json" \
        -H "Content-Type: application/json"\
        -H "X-Auth-Token: $token" | python -m json.tool</programlisting></para>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Positional argument:</emphasis></para>
                <para>
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><parameter>id</parameter>. The ID of the network for which you want to show information. To
                                determine the network ID, issue a <command>neutron</command>
                                <option>network-list</option> command. </para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </para>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Output:</emphasis></para>
                <para>The API operation returns a response body as shown in the following output:</para>

                <programlisting language="json"><?db-font-size 75%?>
                        <xi:include href="../../common/samples/networks-get-detail-resp.json" parse="text"/></programlisting>
            </step>
        </procedure>
